# WORKFLOW

Follow this routine:

## INIT
- Request an L1 and study all L1/L2 content.
- Ask only unanswered questions.

## START
1. Create a short git branch (≤3 words) based on the L1.
2. Mark L1 as WIP.

## LOOP (per L2, in order)
1. If the L2 requires confirmation, ask; else proceed.
2. Take next TODO L2 → set WIP.
3. Implement only this L2:
   - Add/update tests.
   - Run tests; if unable, stop and ask.
   - Fix failures until all pass.
4. `git add` all changes; commit with title + description referencing the L2.
5. Mark L2 DONE.
6. Repeat until all L2 entries are DONE.

## END
- Mark L1 DONE.
- If needed add concise docs to `AGENTS.md` (LLM-oriented).
- Notify user with a brief summary.
- Support interactive refinement until user declares the work complete.

